\pard\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf1\b Significant changes\b0  in this version of PTXprint which you might want to be aware of:\cf0\par
\par
\cf2 (1) On the \b Layout\b0  tab:\par
* \b Variable Line Spacing \b0 is a new option which works with \b Fill Columns \b0 to help fill the page\par
* \b Notelines \b0 allows you to create ruled or dotted lines in the wide gutter area (Journaling Bible)\par
\cf0\par
\cf3 (2) On the \b Advanced \b0 tab:\par
* All the TeXpert hacks have been moved to the 'Other' tab (at the top)\par
* These settings can now also be found when searching\par
* Options that are not set to the default value appear in bold\par
\par
\cf4 (3) On the \b Pictures \b0 tab:\par
* Much of the underlying code has been re-written to be more reliable, but with only limited testing, expect to encounter minor issues (and please report them).\par
\cf0\b\par
"Bible Layout For Everyone"\b0  - Easily create scripture PDFs for trial publications\par
\par
PTXprint is an easy-to-use program which harnesses the power of extended macros from PTX2PDF which is a XeTeX based macro package for typesetting USFM formatted (Paratext) scripture files.\par
\par
PTXprint is available for both Linux and Windows from the main home page: {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://software.sil.org/ptxprint/download }}{\fldrslt{https://software.sil.org/ptxprint/download\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20  \par
It is 64-bit software and will NOT run on 32-bit versions of Windows. It is recommended to be used with Paratext 9.x (or later), but can also work even if Paratext is NOT installed. It is not part of the Paratext updates ecosystem, so does not get automatically updated. Please check the PTXprint home page regularly for updated versions.\par
\par
There is a category dedicated to PTXprint issues on ({{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://support.bible/PTXprint }}{\fldrslt{https://support.bible/PTXprint\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 ) where you can get assistance from other PTXprint users.\par
\par
Please use "New Issue" button in the GitHub Issue Tracking System ({{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://github.com/sillsdev/ptx2pdf/issues }}{\fldrslt{https://github.com/sillsdev/ptx2pdf/issues\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 ) to report any bugs, or document suggestions for improvement. \par
\par
If you serve in a sensitive location, you can report issues directly by e-mail <{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:ptxprint_support@sil.org" }}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf5\cf6\ul ptxprint_support@sil.org}}}}\f0\fs20 > rather than via the publicly accessible websites listed above.\par
\par
